      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): Avoid keyring prompt storms",
        "body": "Keychain-backed reads can currently fan out into extra prompts in read-oriented commands. `auth tokens export` uses the normal token getter, which can migrate legacy default-client tokens by writing a primary key and reading it back, and `auth list` falls back to per-token probing after a keyring timeout.\n\nThis changes export to use a read-only token path when the store supports it, keeps legacy migration for normal token reads, and stops `auth list` fallback probing once the keyring has already timed out. It also preserves the actual legacy-read error when the primary key is missing but the legacy key read fails.\n\nThe user-facing effect is that export/list paths avoid turning one blocked Keychain operation into multiple password prompts while retaining existing legacy-token compatibility.\n",
        "branch": "lox/keyring-export-prompt-hardening",
